        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 14 at 8:54PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 854 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Centenary, or 13 miles north of Buckingham, moving east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small trees and blow around
unsecured objects. Wind impacting handling of high profile
vehicles. Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Fork Union around 905 PM EDT.
Columbia around 915 PM EDT.
Fife around 925 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Dixie, Hatchers,
Ashby, Stage Junction, Three Square, Shores, Central Plains, Bremo
Bluff, Clinton, and Tamworth.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 100 AM EDT for
central Virginia.</instruction>
